  "readme_html": "\n        \n          <p>Yarn Llama 2 is a model based on <a href=\"https://ollama.ai/library/llama2\" rel=\"nofollow\">Llama2</a> that extends its context size up to 128k context. It is developed by <a href=\"https://nousresearch.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">Nous Research</a> by implementing the YaRN method to further train the model to support larger context windows.</p>\n\n<h2>CLI</h2>\n\n<p>64k context size:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ollama run yarn-llama2\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>128k context size:</p>\n\n<pre><code>ollama run yarn-llama2:7b-128k\n</code></pre>\n\n<h2>API</h2>\n\n<p>Example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>curl -X POST http://localhost:11434/api/generate -d &#39;{\n  &#34;model&#34;: &#34;yarn-llama2:7b-128k&#34;,\n  &#34;prompt&#34;:&#34;Here is a story about llamas eating grass&#34;\n }&#39;\n</code></pre>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://huggingface.co/NousResearch/Yarn-Llama-2-7b-64k\" rel=\"nofollow\">Hugging Face</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2309.00071.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">YaRN: Efficient Context Window Extension of Large\nLanguage Models</a></p>\n\n        \n      ",
